{
  "text": "TaqMan\u00ae Fast Universal PCR 2x Master Mix (ThermoFisher Scientific). Primers were used at 500nM and hydrolysis probes at 125nM final concentrations (primer and probe sequences are shown in Table 2 [CITATION_1] ). The qPCR was run on a 7500 Fast Real Time System (Applied Biosystems) with the following cycle profile: 95 \u00b0C for 1 mins and then 40 cycles at 95 \u00b0C for 10 sec and 60 \u00b0C for 30 sec. IBV 5\u2032UTR primer and hydrolysis probe sequences were as follows: IBV5\u2032 Forward, 5\u2032-GCTTTTGAGCCTAGCGTT-3\u2032; IBV5\u2032",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "32383513"
